Not really a minor fix, and not on i would expect to see implemented.<P>Just one for isntance. you take your level 22 druid into camelot, but you drop upon zoning, or purposely release him in the city walls. How many of the so called guards in there ae coded to actually guard anything? We don't know because they ahev never been needed for that purpose. there may be NO guard code whatsoever and this druid now runs rampant killing everyone in sight.<P>Same with ging into a dungeon. Once there, say you release a ept, or drop. where does it go? there is no home point for it to return to as its home point is in another zone entirely. <P>Just too much to worry about. Instead i think maing more targets charmable, especially inside dungeons. so I guess we just have to wait a patch or two and see.<P>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
