<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
From the design standpoint allowing more MOBs in the dungeons to be chanmed is a much better option. then they could also tailor the dungeon for challenge, without having someone come in with a pet that woudl totally throw off hunting.<P>Example?<P>Are these undead in most dungeons vulnerable to fire? If so, imagine taking a Thaumaturge that starts every fight with a big NPC type fire blast. This is normally a bit higher than a typical PC will be doing at that level, and if there is a bonus on fire damage this could wreck things badly.<P>Also, that means EVERY zone must have EVERY Model and EVERY skin loaded then. This is one of the main reasons games are compartmentalized like this, to cut down memory requirements.<P>Let's just see what we can charm when the changes come along. more will be added for us, but who can say what?<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
</FONT>
